  "prompt": "Which is the best web designing company in Delhi & around India?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" web designing company can be subjective and depends on your specific needs, budget, and project requirements. However, here are some highly reputed web design companies in Delhi and around India known for their quality work and client satisfaction:\n\n### **Top Web Designing Companies in Delhi & India**\n1. **Webkul Software Pvt. Ltd.**\n   - Known for innovative web design and development, especially for eCommerce and business websites.\n   - Location: Noida, Delhi-NCR.\n\n2. **Delhi Web Promotion**\n   - Offers end-to-end web design, development, and digital marketing services.\n   - Location: Delhi.\n\n3. **Cub Habits Media**\n   - Specializes in creative web design, UI/UX, and responsive websites.\n   - Location: Delhi.\n\n4. **Octal Info Solution**\n   - Provides custom web design, mobile app development, and digital solutions.\n   - Location: Jaipur (with a presence in Delhi).\n\n5. **Mobikasa**\n   - A leading web design and development company with a focus on mobile-first and responsive designs.\n   - Location: Delhi-NCR.\n\n6. **Hike Commerce**\n   - Known for eCommerce web design and development solutions.\n   - Location: Delhi.\n\n7. **Dot Com Infoway**\n   - Offers web design, development, and digital marketing services to clients globally.\n   - Location: Chennai (with a presence in Delhi).\n\n8. **Radon Media**\n   - Specializes in creative web design with a focus on startups and small businesses.\n   - Location: Delhi.\n\n9. **SAG IPL**\n   - Provides website design, development, and IT consulting services.\n   - Location: Delhi.\n\n10. **The NineHertz**\n    - Known for custom web design, mobile app development, and game development.\n    - Location: Jaipur (with a presence in Delhi).\n\n### **How to Choose the Best Web Designing Company**\n1. **Portfolio**: Review their past work to ensure their design style aligns with your vision.\n2. **Expertise**: Check if they specialize in the type of website you need (e.g., eCommerce, corporate, or portfolio).\n3. **Client Reviews**: Look for testimonials or case studies to gauge their reputation.\n4. **Budget**: Ensure their pricing fits your budget without compromising quality.\n5. **Communication**: Choose a company that maintains clear and transparent communication.\n\nBefore finalizing, consider contacting multiple companies to discuss your project and get a sense of their approach and professionalism.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
